vanguard /ˈvænˌɡɑːd/

N-SING If someone is in the vanguard of something such as a revolution or an area of research, they are involved in the most advanced part of it. You can also refer to the people themselves as the vanguard . 先锋 

例： Students and intellectuals have been in the vanguard of revolutionary change in China. 学生和知识分子一直是中国革命变革的先锋。

